@Reasoning
Returns the digest output length in bytes for hash algorithm alg, or 0 if
alg is not a hash. BLAKE2b is documented at its two default lengths
(BLAKE2B_256 = 32, BLAKE2B_512 = 64). BLAKE2s has variable output; the
default registered here is 32. BLAKE3 has XOF-extendable output; the
registered default is 32 bytes.

Sizes per FIPS 180-4 / FIPS 202 / RFC 7693 / BLAKE3 spec:
  SHA2-256:    32
  SHA2-384:    48
  SHA2-512:    64
  SHA3-256:    32
  SHA3-384:    48
  SHA3-512:    64
  BLAKE3:      32     (default; XOF supports more)
  BLAKE2B-256: 32
  BLAKE2B-512: 64
  BLAKE2S:     32
  KECCAK-256:  32
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Lookup by integer comparison.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Non-secret metadata. Hash output length validation is essential when
hashes are concatenated or used as commitments; mismatched lengths can
enable length-extension or domain-separation attacks.
@End Security_Scope
