@Reasoning
Returns the AEAD tag length in bytes for AEAD algorithm alg, or 0 if alg
is not an AEAD scheme. All currently registered AEADs use a 16-byte
authentication tag (128-bit security against forgery), per their respective
RFCs and SP 800-38D.

  AES-GCM (all variants):  16
  AES-GCM-SIV:             16
  ChaCha20-Poly1305:       16
  XChaCha20-Poly1305:      16
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Lookup by integer comparison.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Tag length is the dominant factor in unforgeability advantage; per SP
800-38D section 5.2.1.2 the AEAD tag must be at least 96 bits (12 bytes)
for any GCM use. Returning the registered length lets callers allocate
tag buffers correctly without leaking it into the algorithm dispatch.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "algorithm_aead_tag_byte_length" takes alg as Integer returns Integer:
