End Process

@Reasoning
Returns the AEAD nonce (IV) length in bytes for AEAD algorithm alg, or 0
if alg is not an AEAD scheme.

Per RFC 8439, SP 800-38D, and libsodium / XChaCha-Poly1305 spec:
  AES-128-GCM:           12
  AES-256-GCM:           12
  AES-128-GCM-SIV:       12
  AES-256-GCM-SIV:       12
  ChaCha20-Poly1305:     12
  XChaCha20-Poly1305:    24
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Lookup by integer comparison.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Nonce length is the dominant factor in the "random nonce" failure mode.
Per SP 800-38D 8.3, a randomly-generated 96-bit IV gives only 2^48 safe
encryptions before a collision is non-negligible; XChaCha20-Poly1305's
192-bit nonce removes that constraint. Returning the registered length
guides nonce.runa toward the correct domain for each algorithm.
@End Security_Scope
