@Reasoning
Returns the nominal security level of alg in BITS. Security bits are the
log2 of the expected number of operations to break the scheme under the
best-known generic or quantum attack, whichever is smaller, per NIST IR
8413 (PQC final report) and FIPS 140-3 strength categories.

Classical:
  Ed25519, X25519, AES-128, SHA-256:                    128
  Ed448, X448, AES-192:                                 224  (Ed448 / X448
                                                              ~ 224-bit per
                                                              RFC 7748/8032)
  ECDSA-P256:                                           128  (per NIST)
  ECDSA-P384, AES-256:                                  192
  ECDSA-P521:                                           256
  RSA-PSS-2048 / RSA-PKCS1v15-2048:                     112  (NIST SP 800-57)
  RSA-PSS-3072 / RSA-PKCS1v15-3072:                     128
  RSA-PSS-4096 / RSA-PKCS1v15-4096:                     152  (between 128 & 192)
  SHA-384, SHA3-384, BLAKE2B-384 (not registered):      192
  SHA-512, SHA3-512, BLAKE2B-512, BLAKE3-extended:      256
  BLAKE3-32, SHA-256, SHA3-256, BLAKE2B-256, KECCAK-256: 128

Post-quantum (NIST category levels per NIST IR 8413):
  ML-KEM-512, ML-DSA-44, SLH-DSA-128S, SLH-DSA-128F, FALCON-512:  128 (cat 1)
  ML-KEM-768, ML-DSA-65, SLH-DSA-192S, SLH-DSA-192F:              192 (cat 3)
  ML-KEM-1024, ML-DSA-87, SLH-DSA-256S, SLH-DSA-256F, FALCON-1024: 256 (cat 5)
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Lookup by integer comparison. Returns 0 for unrecognized identifiers; an
authorization-style "minimum security" check MUST treat 0 as below any
positive threshold.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Non-secret metadata. Used by policy enforcement (minimum security bits per
operation type) but the algorithm tag itself is not secret.

References:
- NIST SP 800-57 Part 1 Rev 5: key length recommendations.
- NIST IR 8413: PQC final round-3 report, security categories.
- RFC 7748: X25519/X448 security claims.
- RFC 8032: Ed25519/Ed448 security claims.
@End Security_Scope
