@Reasoning
Returns 1 if alg supports cryptographic aggregation (signature aggregation
or multi-recipient KEM combining) per a published scheme; 0 otherwise.

Currently:
  - Ed25519 supports BIP-340-style Schnorr aggregation under the
    MuSig2 protocol (Nick, Ruffing, Seurin 2021); the underlying group
    operations are exposed by ed25519.runa.
  - No other Tier-1 algorithm has an aggregation scheme in this Runa
    crypto suite yet. RSA, ECDSA, and the PQ signatures return 0.

Returns 0 by default for forward compatibility; callers must NOT assume
a 1 result implies any specific aggregation protocol.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 1 only for ALG_ED25519. All others return 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Non-secret metadata.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "algorithm_supports_aggregation" takes alg as Integer returns Integer:
    If alg is equal to ALG_ED25519:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SECTION 5: Hash-algorithm-specific dispatcher helpers
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Internal helper to map an algorithm tag to the hash_id integer expected by
ecdsa.runa and rsa.runa. The internal hash_id space is a smaller dense set
defined inside those modules; this helper provides the bridge so callers
can write algorithm-tag-driven code without leaking the internal numbering.

Mapping:
  ALG_SHA2_256 -> 1
  ALG_SHA2_384 -> 2
  ALG_SHA2_512 -> 3
  ALG_SHA3_256 -> 11
  ALG_SHA3_384 -> 12
  ALG_SHA3_512 -> 13
  ALG_BLAKE3   -> 20
Other hashes return -1 (unsupported by ecdsa/rsa dispatchers).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Lookup by integer comparison.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Non-secret. Returning -1 forces callers to reject; never selects a default.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "algorithm_to_hash_id" takes alg as Integer returns Integer:
    If alg is equal to ALG_SHA2_256:
        Return 1
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_SHA2_384:
        Return 2
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_SHA2_512:
        Return 3
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_SHA3_256:
        Return 11
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_SHA3_384:
        Return 12
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_SHA3_512:
        Return 13
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_BLAKE3:
        Return 20
    End If
    Return 0 minus 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Map an RSA signature algorithm tag to the rsa.runa module's internal hash
identifier. The RSA module exposes a small dense set of hash ids (0 = SHA-256,
1 = SHA-384, 2 = SHA-512); this helper is the bridge from the algorithm-tag
space (ALG_RSA_PKCS1V15_SHAxxx_yyyy / ALG_RSA_PSS_SHAxxx_yyyy) to those ids.

Returns -1 for any non-RSA-signature tag. Callers MUST treat -1 as a hard
reject; this is the policy gate for any RSA hash that is not SHA-2 256/384/512.

Mapping:
  ALG_RSA_PKCS1V15_SHA256_*  -> 0
  ALG_RSA_PKCS1V15_SHA384_*  -> 1
  ALG_RSA_PKCS1V15_SHA512_*  -> 2
  ALG_RSA_PSS_SHA256_*       -> 0
  ALG_RSA_PSS_SHA384_*       -> 1
  ALG_RSA_PSS_SHA512_*       -> 2
  Anything else              -> -1
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Lookup by integer comparison; no allocation.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Non-secret metadata. Returning -1 prevents silent hash-default substitution.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rsa_alg_to_rsa_hash_id" takes alg as Integer returns Integer:
    If alg is equal to ALG_RSA_PKCS1V15_SHA256_2048:
        Return 0
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_RSA_PKCS1V15_SHA256_3072:
        Return 0
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_RSA_PKCS1V15_SHA256_4096:
        Return 0
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_RSA_PSS_SHA256_2048:
        Return 0
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_RSA_PSS_SHA256_3072:
        Return 0
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_RSA_PSS_SHA256_4096:
        Return 0
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_RSA_PKCS1V15_SHA384_2048:
        Return 1
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_RSA_PKCS1V15_SHA384_3072:
        Return 1
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_RSA_PKCS1V15_SHA384_4096:
        Return 1
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_RSA_PSS_SHA384_2048:
        Return 1
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_RSA_PSS_SHA384_3072:
        Return 1
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_RSA_PSS_SHA384_4096:
        Return 1
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_RSA_PKCS1V15_SHA512_2048:
        Return 2
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_RSA_PKCS1V15_SHA512_3072:
        Return 2
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_RSA_PKCS1V15_SHA512_4096:
        Return 2
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_RSA_PSS_SHA512_2048:
        Return 2
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_RSA_PSS_SHA512_3072:
        Return 2
    End If
    If alg is equal to ALG_RSA_PSS_SHA512_4096:
        Return 2
    End If
    Return 0 minus 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Returns 1 if alg is an RSASSA-PSS tag, 0 if it is an RSA-PKCS#1 v1.5 tag, and
-1 if alg is not an RSA signature tag at all. Used by rsa_verify_from_spki to
dispatch between rsa_pss_verify and rsa_pkcs1v15_verify without re-enumerating
every (hash, modulus) variant in the caller.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
PSS slots occupy 120..128; PKCS#1 v1.5 slots occupy 110..118.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1). Two range comparisons.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Non-secret metadata. -1 forces hard reject in the caller.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rsa_alg_is_pss" takes alg as Integer returns Integer:
    If alg is less than 110:
        Return 0 minus 1
    End If
    If alg is greater than 128:
        Return 0 minus 1
    End If
    If alg is greater than 119:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Returns the RSA modulus length in bytes encoded by the algorithm tag, or 0 if
alg is not an RSA signature tag. The byte length is 256 for 2048-bit, 384 for
3072-bit, 512 for 4096-bit moduli.

Used by certificate.runa and signature.runa for cross-checking the modulus
length read from the SubjectPublicKeyInfo against the modulus length declared
by the algorithm tag.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
The RSA tag slot layout encodes modulus in the low three slots of each
9-tag (hash, modulus) family: offset 0..2 -> 2048, 3..5 -> 3072, 6..8 -> 4096.
A range-and-modulo computation extracts the modulus index without an explicit
table; the result is multiplied to bytes.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
O(1). One range check plus arithmetic.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Non-secret metadata. Returning 0 forces hard reject in any caller doing a
modulus cross-check.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "rsa_alg_modulus_bytes" takes alg as Integer returns Integer:
    If alg is less than 110:
        Return 0
    End If
    If alg is greater than 128:
        Return 0
    End If
    Note: Map each tag to its slot offset within its 9-slot family.
    Let family_base be 110
    If alg is greater than 118:
        Set family_base to 120
    End If
    Let slot be alg minus family_base
    Note: slot 0..2 -> 256, 3..5 -> 384, 6..8 -> 512.
    Let modulus_index be slot modulo by 3
    If modulus_index is equal to 0:
        Return 256
    End If
    If modulus_index is equal to 1:
        Return 384
    End If
    If modulus_index is equal to 2:
        Return 512
    End If
    Return 0
End Process
